===============================
Terraform CLI Commands
===============================

Core Workflow
----------------
terraform init       - Initialize working directory and download providers
terraform plan       - Preview changes before applying
terraform apply      - Apply changes to reach desired state
terraform destroy    - Remove all managed infrastructure
terraform validate   - Check configuration syntax

Formatting & Cleanup
------------------------
terraform fmt        - Format .tf files to canonical style
terraform taint      - Mark a resource for recreation
terraform untaint    - Remove taint from a resource

State & Output Management
----------------------------
terraform show       - Display current state or saved plan
terraform output     - Show output values
terraform state      - Advanced state file operations
terraform refresh    - Sync state with real infrastructure

Debugging & Exploration
--------------------------
terraform console    - Interactive shell for evaluating expressions
terraform graph      - Generate dependency graph (Graphviz format)

Workspace & Module Management
-------------------------------
terraform workspace  - Manage multiple environments
terraform get        - Download referenced modules
terraform import     - Bring existing resources under Terraform control

Authentication & Remote Backends
-----------------------------------
terraform login      - Authenticate with Terraform Cloud
terraform logout     - Remove stored credentials

Tip: Use 'terraform plan -out=tfplan' and 'terraform apply tfplan' for safer deployments.
